e. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn21"></a><a href="#_ftnref21">[21]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> Ibid</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn22"></a><a href="#_ftnref22">[22]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> Becker H, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">Stuifbergen</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> A, Tinkle M. Reproductive health care experiences of women with physical disabilities: a qualitative study. Arch Phys Med </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">Rehabil</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">. 1997 Dec;78(12 </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">Suppl</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> 5):S26-33.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn23"></a><a href="#_ftnref23">[23]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">Basnet</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">Machhindra</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> et al. “Describing disabled women's access and experience of maternal health care in rural </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">Makwanpur</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">, Nepal”. Presentation on Centre for International Health and Development. University College London. Accessed on November 28, 2013. www.lcint.org/download.php?id=958</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn24"></a><a href="#_ftnref24">[24]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> Ibid</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn25"></a><a href="#_ftnref25">[25]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> World Bank. 2011.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn26"></a><a href="#_ftnref26">[26]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> WHO/UNFPA. 2009.</span></p><p sty